==English==
===Etymology===
'''[[dude]]''' + '''[[-ly]]'''

===Adjective===
'''dudely'''
# Of or pertaining to a [[dude]] (in various senses).

===Quotations===
* '''1992,''' Autumn Stephens, ''Wild Women''  [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0943233364&id=hmwn1H2xDZ0C&pg=PA56&lpg=PA56&dq=dudely&sig=U0EwnTGCeNfKYFgcVSgVCNkDoN0]
*: Long before the slinky Miss Shields was a twinkle in her mama’s eye, nothing came between erstwhile Southern belle Elsa Jane Guerin and her '''dudely''' duds.
* '''2001,''' Stephen Beachy, ''Distortion'' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN1560239980&id=U1N20gh2p-MC&pg=PA268&lpg=PA268&dq=dudely&sig=zXwiJUJHq_brxfa-MBKQt4aev-o]
*: I love bad whiteboys, the really skanky sort of white-trash ones, you know, the ones that surf or live in the woods or just got out of prison, the '''dudely''' ones who’re sort of closeted but really straight-acting, those are the ones I always fall for.
* '''2003,''' Carole Nelson Douglas, ''Cat in a Neon Nightmare'' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0765345927&id=8RAgHGxxkvMC&pg=PA213&lpg=PA213&dq=dudely&sig=sM26a3VIHWgQWagqwbRFqXdkkhQ]
